[♪...]

00:46.004 --> 00:48.590
Bessie: "FROM HONEYCOMB TO HIVE:

00:48.673 --> 00:51.134
THE MIRIAM BREEDLOVE STORY."

00:51.217 --> 00:55.972
{\an1}OH, HAPPY, OUR FIRST FILM
PREMIERE IN JUST THREE HOURS.

00:56.055 --> 00:59.100
AREN'T YOU EXCITED
TO BE MY PLUS ONE?

00:59.184 --> 01:00.059
[JOYFUL BARK]

01:00.143 --> 01:01.895
[PANTING]

01:01.978 --> 01:04.772
NOW HAPPY, WE SHOULD
ARRIVE AT THE PREMIERE

01:04.855 --> 01:06.441
NO LESS THAN 90 MINUTES
BEFORE SHOWTIME.

01:06.524 --> 01:08.401
THAT'LL GIVE US
A HALF AN HOUR ON THE RED CARPET

01:08.485 --> 01:10.528
{\an1}FOR INTERVIEWS
AND PRESS AND PHOTOS...

01:10.612 --> 01:13.907
{\an5}...BEFORE WE TAKE
OUR V.I.P. SEATS
IN THE FRONT ROW.

01:13.990 --> 01:16.367
DON'T WORRY, I'VE ALREADY
THOUGHT ABOUT SNACKS.

01:16.451 --> 01:18.369
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYS]

01:18.453 --> 01:19.329
[BABY CRIES]

01:19.412 --> 01:21.915
[♪...]

01:21.998 --> 01:24.375
[EXCITED BARKING]

01:27.128 --> 01:28.755
HAPPY, IT'S FOUR DOLLAR SIGNS.

01:28.838 --> 01:30.840
I'M NOT MADE OF MONEY.

01:30.924 --> 01:32.425
[PLAINTIVE BARKING]

01:32.509 --> 01:35.970
YOU HAVE PLENTY OF TOYS AT HOME
THAT YOU NEVER EVEN PLAY WITH.

01:36.054 --> 01:38.807
THAT OLD SOCK,
THAT PLASTIC WATER BOTTLE...

01:38.890 --> 01:41.518
THAT RAISIN UNDER THE COUCH.

01:41.601 --> 01:44.354
[EXASPERATED BARKING]

01:44.437 --> 01:47.357
[ANGRY BARKING]

01:47.440 --> 01:51.444
[LOUD TANTRUM CONTINUES...]

01:51.528 --> 01:54.656
LET'S GO, MISTER.

01:56.407 --> 01:58.535
OH, HAPPY,
THE LIMP NOODLE?

01:58.618 --> 02:00.411
I TAUGHT YOU
THAT ONE... PLEASE.

02:00.495 --> 02:03.832
[PLEADING BARKING]

02:03.915 --> 02:05.917
Bessie: END OF
DISCUSSION, HAPPY.

02:06.000 --> 02:07.544
YOU ARE NOT GETTING
THAT OVERPRICED BONE.

02:07.627 --> 02:10.128
{\an3}[GROWLING]

02:10.213 --> 02:11.965
NOW, IF YOU WILL EXCUSE ME

02:12.048 --> 02:14.801
I HAVE A PREMIERE
TO GET READY FOR.

02:14.884 --> 02:15.343
[GROWLING]

02:20.390 --> 02:24.352
Bessie: ♪ 'CAUSE I'M RUNNIN'
WITH THE RAINBOW UNICORN... ♪

02:24.435 --> 02:25.395
[GROWLS]

02:25.478 --> 02:27.564
{\an6}♪ DON'T YOU WISH
YOU WERE ME? ♪

02:25.478 --> 02:27.564
{\an1}[GRUNTS]

02:27.647 --> 02:29.107
♪ GET DOWN HERE, BESSIE ♪

02:29.190 --> 02:31.651
♪ LA, LA, LA, LA,
LA, LA-LA... ♪

02:31.734 --> 02:33.319
♪ LA-LA-LA, LA, LA... ♪

02:33.403 --> 02:35.363
Bessie: THANK YOU,
THANK YOU, AHH.

02:35.446 --> 02:37.407
Bessie: ♪ 'CAUSE I'M RUNNIN...
[BEATBOXING] ♪

02:37.490 --> 02:38.575
♪ WITH THE RAINBOW
[BEATBOXING]... ♪

02:38.658 --> 02:40.618
♪ U-NI-CORN... [BEATBOXING] ♪

02:40.702 --> 02:44.455
[♪...]

02:44.539 --> 02:47.500
GENUINE PRESCRIPTION GLASSES.

02:47.584 --> 02:48.877
ALL RIGHT...

02:48.960 --> 02:50.336
{\an1}...DEAL.

02:53.840 --> 02:55.258
[BESSIE BEATBOXING]

02:55.341 --> 02:56.175
♪ REMIX! 'CAUSE I'M RUNNIN'...
[BEATBOXING] ♪

02:56.259 --> 02:57.760
♪ WITH THE RAINBOW
[BEATBOXING] ♪

02:57.844 --> 03:00.930
♪ U-NI-CORN [BEATBOXING] ♪

03:01.014 --> 03:02.515
♪ DON'T YOU WISH YOU WERE ME? ♪

03:02.599 --> 03:04.058
[FAUCET SQUEAKS OFF...
WATER DRIPPING]

03:04.142 --> 03:06.644
Bessie: WHA... WHAT?

03:08.688 --> 03:09.522
WHERE ARE THEY?

03:09.606 --> 03:12.442
{\an1}WHAT, I CAN'T...
I CAN'T FIND MY GLASSES.

03:12.525 --> 03:15.111
WHERE... MY GLASSES!

03:15.194 --> 03:17.280
[CARNIVAL MUSIC PLAYS]

03:22.785 --> 03:25.830
[YAWNING]

03:28.917 --> 03:29.334
[CHUCKLES SHYLY]

03:32.045 --> 03:32.629
[GRUNTING] LET ME GET...

03:32.712 --> 03:34.380
[SIGHS]

03:37.675 --> 03:39.052
HAPPY, HAPPY,
WHERE ARE YOU?

03:39.135 --> 03:41.220
EMERGENCY, I CAN'T
FIND MY GLASSES.

03:41.304 --> 03:42.263
WHA!

03:47.852 --> 03:50.813
OH, THERE YOU ARE.

03:50.897 --> 03:52.231
HELP ME FIND MY GLASSES.

03:52.315 --> 03:53.775
{\an3}HOW AM I GONNA SEE
AT THE PREMIERE?

03:55.693 --> 03:57.862
HM, THE SILENT TREATMENT?

03:57.946 --> 03:59.113
REAL MATURE.

03:59.197 --> 04:00.490
{\an3}WELL, FINE, I'LL JUST
FIND 'EM MYSELF.

04:00.573 --> 04:02.116
{\an1}FINDING MY GLASSES-
NO NEED TO PANIC.

04:02.200 --> 04:06.329
GLASSES WILL BE FOUND
AND... NOPE.

04:06.412 --> 04:08.831
AH, LET'S SEE... NO.

04:08.915 --> 04:11.167
[PANTING] NO!

04:08.915 --> 04:11.167
{\an1}[CRASH]

04:11.250 --> 04:13.252
WHERE ARE THEY?

04:18.675 --> 04:21.177
EXCUSE ME, SIR?

04:21.260 --> 04:23.513
{\an5}UM, PARDON ME, MA'AM,
JUST A SEC,
HAVE YOU SEEN A PAIR...

04:23.596 --> 04:25.556
I NEED EVERYONE'S ATTENTION.

04:25.640 --> 04:27.350
HAS ANYONE SEEN MY GLASSES?

04:27.433 --> 04:30.603
I'M GOING TO A MOVIE PREMIERE
IN JUST TWO HOURS.

04:30.687 --> 04:35.024
WELL, EVERYONE'S TOO BUSY TO
HELP A SIGHT-IMPAIRED CHILD.

04:35.108 --> 04:36.442
REAL, REAL NICE.

04:36.526 --> 04:39.112
I WILL TAKE MYSELF TO THE
GLASSES STORE THEN.

04:40.947 --> 04:43.199
OOH, IT'S NIPPY OUT HERE.

04:43.282 --> 04:43.491
I BETTER GET A HAT.

04:46.744 --> 04:47.745
[SOUNDS OF TRAFFIC]

04:47.829 --> 04:50.206
OK, NO PROBLEM.

04:50.289 --> 04:51.833
THIS IS THE PERFECT OPPORTUNITY

04:51.916 --> 04:55.128
TO EMPLOY MY OTHER FOUR
HIGHLY DEVELOPED SENSES.

04:56.170 --> 04:58.047
[HORN HONKING]

04:58.131 --> 04:59.882
[DISTANT SIREN WAILS]

05:02.927 --> 05:03.803
AH, JUST AS I THOUGHT.

05:03.886 --> 05:05.930
THE MAILBOX ON THE CORNER.

05:06.014 --> 05:08.391
GOOD, ON COURSE.

05:08.474 --> 05:12.437
BUSHES... GETTING WARMER.

05:12.520 --> 05:13.730
...AND BIRDS.

05:13.813 --> 05:14.731
THE PARK.

05:14.814 --> 05:16.107
I'LL TAKE THE TUNNEL.

05:18.985 --> 05:19.527
[TIRES SQUEAL]

05:22.030 --> 05:26.617
[♪...]

05:26.701 --> 05:27.994
[BIKE BELL DINGS]

05:28.077 --> 05:29.620
[♪...]

05:32.623 --> 05:33.708
[CHUCKLES]

05:37.628 --> 05:39.422
[REVERSE ALERT BEEPS]

05:39.505 --> 05:41.758
Bessie: MM, THE PARK
SMELLS AWESOME.

05:41.841 --> 05:45.094
[♪...]

05:45.178 --> 05:46.637
Bessie: FRISBEE, INCOMING!

05:46.721 --> 05:47.388
GO LONG.

05:56.105 --> 05:57.440
HUH? [RETCHES]

05:59.192 --> 06:01.527
OK, OUT OF THE PARK,
JUST A FEW MORE BLOCKS.

06:01.611 --> 06:05.198
THEN IT'S GLASSES, GLASSES,
GLASSES, PREMIERE.

06:05.698 --> 06:07.658
[GRUNTS]

06:07.742 --> 06:08.826
OH, EXCUSE ME, SIR.

06:08.910 --> 06:10.411
DO YOU HAVE THE TIME?

06:10.495 --> 06:13.247
I AM ATTENDING A WORLD PREMIERE
THIS EVENING.

06:16.501 --> 06:18.795
HUH, SORRY TO HAVE
DISTURBED YOU.

06:18.878 --> 06:20.880
SOMEBODY'S UPSET 'CAUSE
THEY WEREN'T INVITED.

06:20.963 --> 06:25.093
[♪...]

06:30.598 --> 06:33.309
[ONLOOKERS GASP DELIGHTEDLY]

06:39.565 --> 06:40.483
All: OHH...

06:47.740 --> 06:48.741
HUH?

06:48.825 --> 06:49.742
PHEW.

06:49.826 --> 06:52.120
WHOA!

06:54.080 --> 06:57.667
[SCREECHING AND YELPING]

06:57.750 --> 07:00.419
[SCREECHING CONTINUES]

07:05.842 --> 07:07.385
{\an1}OH!

07:16.519 --> 07:19.522
{\an5}WELL, I'M GONNA
DO CULOTTES
FOR THE RED CARPET

07:19.605 --> 07:23.025
{\an6}WHICH MEANS YOU
CAN TOTALLY RENT
MY METALLIC MINI-DRESS

07:23.109 --> 07:24.694
BUT NOT OVERNIGHT 'CAUSE YOUR
HOUSE SMELLS LIKE CAT BOX.

07:25.611 --> 07:27.363
All: AHH!

07:27.446 --> 07:28.739
PORTIA?

07:28.823 --> 07:30.491
OH, THANK GOODNESS,
IT'S YOU GUYS.

07:30.575 --> 07:34.328
{\an3}I LOST MY GLASSES AND NATURALLY
I NEED PERFECT VISION FOR...

07:34.412 --> 07:36.706
"FROM HONEYCOMB TO HIVE:

07:36.789 --> 07:39.041
THE MIRIAM BREEDLOVE STORY."

07:39.125 --> 07:39.959
{\an3}HEY, CAN YOU GUYS POINT ME
TO THE GLASSES STORE?

07:40.042 --> 07:43.171
SURE, BESSIE.

07:43.254 --> 07:44.964
WE WOULDN'T WANT YOU TO MISS

07:45.047 --> 07:47.300
THE FIRST-EVER HONEYBEE
WORLD PREMIERE.

07:47.383 --> 07:49.468
THERE YOU GO.

07:49.552 --> 07:50.887
SEE YOU TONIGHT.

07:50.970 --> 07:51.429
Bessie: THANKS GUYS.

07:51.512 --> 07:52.638
[GIRLS SNICKERING]

07:54.015 --> 07:57.018
[WATER GURGLING]

07:57.101 --> 07:58.186
BOY, THEY REALLY JAZZED
THIS PLACE UP.

07:58.269 --> 07:59.770
[MUSIC PLAYS ON HEADPHONES]

07:59.854 --> 08:01.189
HELLO?

08:01.272 --> 08:03.774
I'M IN NEED OF ASSISTANCE.

08:03.858 --> 08:05.526
I'D LIKE TO REPLACE MY GLASSES.

08:07.320 --> 08:09.614
I BELIEVE YOU HAVE
MY PRESCRIPTION ON FILE.

08:13.993 --> 08:16.746
[FISH SNAPPING]

08:16.829 --> 08:18.372
[HAPPY HOWLS]

08:27.506 --> 08:29.342
PHEW... AH!

08:31.928 --> 08:34.388
[BARKS]

08:37.015 --> 08:38.558
[LOW GROWL]

08:45.024 --> 08:47.610
HUH?

08:47.693 --> 08:49.570
[HORN HONKS]

08:51.072 --> 08:51.489
[YELPS]

08:51.572 --> 08:54.116
IS ANYONE HERE?

08:54.200 --> 08:55.368
CAN I GET SOME SERVICE, PLEASE?

08:55.451 --> 08:58.621
OH, I WOULD NOT MIND FILLING OUT

08:58.704 --> 08:59.789
A BRIEF CUSTOMER SATISFACTION
SURVEY AFTER THIS.

08:59.872 --> 09:02.375
AND I DON'T KNOW IF I WOULD
WRITE SOMETHING GOOD.

09:06.045 --> 09:06.671
[WHIMPERING]

09:18.891 --> 09:21.102
[MARCHING BAND PLAYS]

09:21.185 --> 09:22.979
[ELEPHANT TRUMPETS]

09:23.062 --> 09:24.981
[TEETH CLICKING]

09:30.236 --> 09:32.863
[MOANING... GASPS]

09:37.076 --> 09:39.078
[GLASS SHATTERS]

09:39.161 --> 09:41.372
MAY I HELP YOU?

09:41.455 --> 09:43.624
UHH...

09:43.708 --> 09:46.335
{\an1}FINALLY, LET ME JUST
CATCH YOU UP ON MY SITUATION.

09:46.419 --> 09:49.672
[MOANING... PANTING]

09:49.755 --> 09:51.841
HEY, MAN, YOU WANNA BE RED?

09:51.924 --> 09:53.801
[PLAINTIVE BARKING]

09:53.884 --> 09:55.344
{\an1}BUT I LOVE THE WORLD
IN THESE GLASSES.

09:55.428 --> 09:58.222
HUH?

09:55.428 --> 09:58.222
{\an1}NO WAY.

09:58.306 --> 10:00.933
[WHINING]

10:01.017 --> 10:01.851
HM?

10:01.934 --> 10:02.935
[FISH GROWLS]

10:03.019 --> 10:04.729
FAR OUT.

10:04.812 --> 10:06.355
DEAL.

10:04.812 --> 10:06.355
[CHOMP]

10:06.439 --> 10:06.814
[GROWLS]

10:08.691 --> 10:10.234
AT WHICH POINT,
I TRIED UNDER THE SOFA.

10:10.318 --> 10:12.611
YOU CAN IMAGINE MY PANIC

10:12.695 --> 10:14.655
SINCE I AM ATTENDING
AN EXCLUSIVE

10:14.739 --> 10:16.782
WORLD <i> PRE...MIERE</i> TONIGHT.

10:19.744 --> 10:20.453
[GASPS]

10:20.536 --> 10:22.413
OH, THANK YOU.

10:22.496 --> 10:24.707
{\an1}THESE ARE JUST
LIKE MY OLD ONES.

10:24.790 --> 10:27.001
[SNIFFS]

10:27.084 --> 10:29.837
YOU EVEN GOT THE SMELL RIGHT.

10:36.218 --> 10:38.554
[SNORING]

10:38.637 --> 10:40.264
HAPS?

10:40.348 --> 10:42.683
I HAVE A PEACE OFFERING.

10:43.392 --> 10:44.810
{\an6}I FOUND IT
ON THE STREET.

10:43.392 --> 10:44.810
[PANTING]

10:44.894 --> 10:45.978
ZERO DOLLAR SIGNS.

10:46.062 --> 10:48.898
HUH?

10:48.981 --> 10:51.442
[LOW GROAN]

11:02.870 --> 11:05.581
AH, BEST SEATS IN THE HOUSE.

11:17.176 --> 11:21.847
[♪...]

11:27.478 --> 11:30.064
Hilary: UH-HUH, YEAH.

11:30.147 --> 11:31.190
NO, I'M LISTENING,
BESSIE, UH-HUH.

11:31.273 --> 11:34.026
NO, KEEP GOING,
UH-HUH, WOW...

11:34.110 --> 11:35.236
{\an1}MOM, MOM,
WATCH ME PRACTICE.

11:35.319 --> 11:36.404
BEN, HONEY, HOLD ON.

11:36.487 --> 11:39.365
Man: Now then, who amongst
you scamps wants porridge?

11:39.448 --> 11:41.826
{\an5}UH-HUH, OK, OK...

11:39.448 --> 11:41.826
OH, ME SIR,
PLEASE, SIR?

11:41.909 --> 11:46.580
Man: Now then, who amongst
you scamps wants porridge?

11:46.664 --> 11:48.457
OH, ME SIR,
PLEASE, SIR.

11:48.541 --> 11:51.627
{\an5}[HAPPY WHISTLES]

11:48.541 --> 11:51.627
[BESSIE ON PHONE IN BACKGROUND]

11:51.710 --> 11:52.586
[BESSIE CONTINUES...]

11:52.670 --> 11:54.130
{\an1}Ben: MOM, MOM,
WATCH ME PRACTICE.

11:54.213 --> 11:55.297
[HAPPY CHUCKLES]

11:55.381 --> 11:56.799
Ben: MOM, MOM...

11:56.882 --> 11:59.343
Bessie: SO BASICALLY,
THESE TECTONIC PLATES

11:59.427 --> 12:01.637
{\an5}ARE LIKE A COUPLE
OF SARDINES WHO DON'T
WANNA BE IN THE SAME CAN

12:01.721 --> 12:03.889
'CAUSE IT'S TOO SMALL-
THERE ISN'T ENOUGH ROOM.

12:03.973 --> 12:06.642
{\an5}AND LIKE IN A MILLION YEARS,
CALIFORNIA'S GONNA FALL
INTO THE OCEAN.

12:06.725 --> 12:07.643
ISN'T THAT COOL, MOM?

12:07.726 --> 12:08.978
Isn't that cool...

12:09.061 --> 12:11.522
{\an1}MOM, MOM, MOM, MOM,
DID YOU TELL HER?

12:11.605 --> 12:12.857
{\an6}OH, OH, AND BEN
HAS HIS BIG AUDITION
AT THEATER CAMP TODAY.

12:15.568 --> 12:17.987
ANYWAY, TELL HAPPY THAT
I LOVE HIM, AND I MISS HIM

12:18.070 --> 12:19.405
AND I GOT HIM A PRESENT.

12:19.488 --> 12:21.490
[ROARS]

12:21.574 --> 12:22.950
DID YOU TELL HIM YET?

12:23.033 --> 12:23.576
[HORN HONKS]

12:23.659 --> 12:25.411
OH, THAT'S THE BEE BUS.

12:25.494 --> 12:26.704
THANKS, MOM, LOVE YOU,
SEE YOU SOON.

12:26.787 --> 12:28.414
DON'T MISS ME,
CATCH YOU ON THE FLIP SIDE.

12:30.249 --> 12:31.584
[HAPPY GRUMBLES]

12:31.667 --> 12:33.169
OH, DID YOU LOSE
SOMETHING, BOY?

12:33.252 --> 12:36.046
HM?

12:41.427 --> 12:43.179
[GASPS]

12:43.262 --> 12:44.847
[STERNLY]: HAPPY.

12:44.930 --> 12:47.516
WHOA, THERE MUST BE
LIKE 50 STEAKS HERE.

12:47.600 --> 12:49.602
[BARKS/PANTS]

12:49.685 --> 12:49.977
500?

12:50.060 --> 12:52.605
500?

12:52.688 --> 12:54.023
THAT'S IT.

12:54.106 --> 12:56.484
{\an4}DROP HAPPY AT
OBEDIENCE SCHOOL
ON YOUR WAY TO CAMP.

12:56.567 --> 12:57.318
AND PUT HIM ON A LEASH.

12:57.401 --> 13:00.196
HUH?

12:57.401 --> 13:00.196
[LAUGHS]

13:00.279 --> 13:01.989
[QUESTIONING BARK]

13:02.072 --> 13:03.282
[GASPS]

13:03.365 --> 13:05.284
YOU ALWAYS GO TOO FAR.

13:05.367 --> 13:07.411
[ALARM BLARES]

13:07.495 --> 13:09.788
[HAPPY GRUMBLES]

13:09.872 --> 13:11.582
COME ON, DOG.

13:11.665 --> 13:13.209
QUICK PIT STOP

13:13.292 --> 13:15.377
THEN I'M TAKING
YOU TO JAIL [LAUGHS].

13:15.461 --> 13:16.587
[COMPLAINING BARK]

13:16.670 --> 13:19.131
[STRAINING GRUNT]

13:19.215 --> 13:20.674
{\an1}OW, OH!

13:21.550 --> 13:24.678
Ben: [MOANING]: OH, OHH...

13:24.762 --> 13:26.013
[SHOP BELL TINKLES]

13:28.307 --> 13:30.309
[COMPLAINING BARK]

13:30.392 --> 13:33.771
{\an3}OH, MAN, OVER
A FEW DOZEN STEAKS?

13:33.854 --> 13:35.731
[BELL TINKLES]

13:35.814 --> 13:36.857
I HEAR YA, MAN.

13:36.941 --> 13:40.236
I HATED OBEDIENCE SCHOOL
THE FIRST COUPLE OF TIMES.

13:40.319 --> 13:41.654
YOU'LL LIVE THROUGH IT.

13:44.114 --> 13:46.408
WOULD A TAQUITO
MAKE YOU FEEL BETTER?

13:46.492 --> 13:47.701
Ben: YES... OOH.

13:47.785 --> 13:50.454
EASY, LITTLE BUDDY,
I GOT YOU COVERED.

13:55.334 --> 13:58.379
[BEEPS... POWERS UP]

14:07.137 --> 14:11.141
[ORGAN PLAYS
"THE ANNIVERSARY SONG"]

14:11.225 --> 14:13.227
[BELCHING GROWL]

14:13.310 --> 14:16.146
[♪...]

14:22.027 --> 14:23.153
[GROANING]

14:25.656 --> 14:26.240
[BEN'S VOICE WHINING]

14:26.323 --> 14:27.866
Happy: HUH?

14:30.911 --> 14:31.829
[SNIFFING]

14:35.165 --> 14:36.250
[BOTH YELP]

14:36.333 --> 14:37.585
[PANTING]

14:37.668 --> 14:39.378
Ben: GROSS.

14:39.461 --> 14:42.047
I... I'M STUCK IN YOUR BODY.

14:44.300 --> 14:46.302
[MOANS]

14:46.385 --> 14:48.053
[CRIES]: OH!

14:48.137 --> 14:48.846
WHAT ABOUT MY AUDITION?

14:48.929 --> 14:51.307
{\an1}WHAT ABOUT YOUR
OBEDIENCE SCHOOL?

14:51.390 --> 14:52.516
WHAT ARE WE GONNA DO?

14:56.228 --> 14:58.272
[MOANING]

14:58.355 --> 15:00.065
[MAN SNORING]

15:00.149 --> 15:01.942
[DOGS BARKING]

15:03.193 --> 15:06.614
{\an3}UH, WE GENERALLY DON'T
BELIEVE IN MUZZLING HERE.

15:06.697 --> 15:09.199
[FRUSTRATED GROANING]

15:09.283 --> 15:11.493
HUH, A LIVE ONE.

15:11.577 --> 15:13.329
DON'T WORRY, WE'LL ISOLATE HIM
IF HE GETS FRESH.

15:13.412 --> 15:16.498
{\an1}[LAUGHING]

15:13.412 --> 15:16.498
{\an3}[BEN MOANS]

15:16.582 --> 15:18.834
Bessie: HAPPY!

15:18.917 --> 15:20.836
HAPPY, HAPPY?

15:20.919 --> 15:24.006
HAPPY,
HAPPY, I'M HOME.

15:24.089 --> 15:25.758
{\an3}HAPPY?

15:25.841 --> 15:26.467
I GOT A PRESENT FOR YOU.

15:26.550 --> 15:28.636
IT'S A BAG OF DIRT.

15:28.719 --> 15:30.346
I MEAN, I DON'T KNOW
WHAT IT IS.

15:30.429 --> 15:32.181
HAPPY?

15:32.264 --> 15:33.432
HAPPY?

15:33.515 --> 15:35.976
HAPPY... [ECHO]?

15:36.060 --> 15:38.020
[♪...]

15:50.824 --> 15:53.285
[GROANS]

15:53.369 --> 15:56.038
[WHIMPERS]

16:05.464 --> 16:08.384
OK, FUR KIDS, MUSH.

16:08.467 --> 16:09.760
[DOGS BARKING]

16:09.843 --> 16:11.470
LET'S GO, FLUBBY.

16:11.553 --> 16:14.223
[STRAINED GROANING]

16:14.306 --> 16:15.849
NO PAIN, NO GAIN.

16:17.393 --> 16:18.977
[GRUNTING...]

16:21.689 --> 16:23.357
AHH...

16:23.440 --> 16:26.193
OK, FLOSSY, GIVE OLD BLOOPER
HERE A LITTLE ENCOURAGEMENT.

16:26.276 --> 16:28.237
[SHOUTS]

16:28.320 --> 16:31.323
[SLURPING]

16:33.033 --> 16:35.786
Bessie: HAPPY?

16:35.869 --> 16:40.040
[HILARY LAUGHING AT TV]

16:40.124 --> 16:40.916
MOM, WHAT'S GOING ON?

16:40.999 --> 16:44.086
IT'S LIKE A GHOST TOWN
AROUND HERE.

16:44.169 --> 16:46.296
AH, I KNOW,
ISN'T IT WONDERFUL?

16:46.380 --> 16:47.297
WHERE'S HAPPY?

16:47.381 --> 16:48.716
OBEDIENCE SCHOOL.

16:48.799 --> 16:50.134
WHAT?

16:50.217 --> 16:52.928
HE TOOK 500 STEAKS
FROM THE CAFE.

16:53.011 --> 16:55.097
WELL, I'M SURE HE WAS PLANNING
ON RETURNING THEM.

16:55.180 --> 16:57.641
OBEDIENCE SCHOOL?

16:57.725 --> 16:59.935
I CANNOT GO AWAY
TO ONE MEASLY FIELD TRIP

17:00.018 --> 17:02.104
WITHOUT MY DOG BEING STRIPPED
OF HIS CIVIL LIBERTIES?

17:02.187 --> 17:03.522
WAS THERE A LAWYER PRESENT?

17:03.605 --> 17:05.190
WAS HE READ HIS RIGHTS?

17:05.273 --> 17:07.483
{\an6}YOU KNOW WHAT, MOM,
HE'S PROBABLY
MISERABLE THERE.

17:07.568 --> 17:09.694
HE'S PROBABLY CRYING

17:09.778 --> 17:12.448
'CAUSE EVERYONE'S TRYING
TO MAKE HIM SO OBEDIENT.

17:12.531 --> 17:14.700
OH, I WILL TAKE IT
FROM HERE, MOM.

17:14.782 --> 17:17.493
HAPPY SLEEPS OUTSIDE TONIGHT.

17:17.578 --> 17:19.954
Bessie: OK, LOVE YOU.

17:20.038 --> 17:21.832
All: ♪ ROW, ROW,
ROW YOUR BOAT ♪

17:21.915 --> 17:23.250
♪ GENTLY DOWN THE STREAM ♪

17:23.333 --> 17:26.127
{\an5}[HAPPY HOWLING]

17:23.333 --> 17:26.127
[LUNCH BELL RINGS]

17:26.211 --> 17:28.130
All: LUNCH!

17:28.213 --> 17:28.922
YEAH?

17:29.006 --> 17:31.508
[CHILDREN LAUGHING AND TALKING]

17:31.592 --> 17:33.302
[♪...]

17:47.483 --> 17:48.484
I BEG YOUR PARDON.

17:48.567 --> 17:50.903
HEY.

17:52.738 --> 17:55.657
[CHILDREN YELLING]

18:00.704 --> 18:02.122
[RETCHING]

18:03.624 --> 18:07.878
Ben: UGH, OHH...

18:07.961 --> 18:09.046
Bessie: HAPPY...

18:09.129 --> 18:11.673
WHAT HAVE THEY
DONE TO YOU, BOY?

18:11.757 --> 18:13.759
Bessie: OH.

18:13.842 --> 18:14.676
[KISS]

18:14.760 --> 18:17.554
OH, MM-MM-MM.

18:17.638 --> 18:20.349
MM-MM, KISSES, KISSES,
KISSES, MWAH.

18:20.432 --> 18:21.975
BESSIE, IT'S ME.

18:22.059 --> 18:24.520
WHAT, BEN?

18:24.603 --> 18:27.272
Ben: I'M IN HERE,
IN THIS CHEAP DOG BODY.

18:30.108 --> 18:31.693
WOW, THAT'S A REALLY GOOD BEN.

18:31.777 --> 18:32.194
DO ME.

18:32.277 --> 18:34.238
BESSIE, IT'S <i> ME.</i>

18:34.321 --> 18:37.115
THE HIPPIE MADE A BATCH OF CRAZY
TAQUITOS IN HIS MAGIC MICROWAVE.

18:37.199 --> 18:39.785
OR MAGIC TAQUITOS
IN HIS CRAZY MICROWAVE.

18:39.868 --> 18:42.663
ANYWAY, I'M HAPPY
AND HAPPY'S ME.

18:47.417 --> 18:49.044
[SPEECHLESS SQUEAKING]

18:49.127 --> 18:51.046
BESSIE, YOU HAVE TO HELP.

18:51.129 --> 18:53.507
I'M GONNA MISS MY BIG AUDITION.

18:53.590 --> 18:54.883
LET ME JUST GET THIS STRAIGHT.

18:54.967 --> 18:57.678
YOU SWITCHED BODIES-
THE OLD SWITCHEROO.

18:57.761 --> 18:58.887
[SIGHS]

18:58.971 --> 19:01.139
[CRYING]

19:01.223 --> 19:04.059
DON'T WORRY, BEN,
WE'RE GONNA FIX THIS.

19:04.143 --> 19:05.936
[HAPPY HOWLING]

19:06.019 --> 19:09.064
HAPPY, YOU'RE SAVED.

19:10.023 --> 19:14.820
{\an3}UGH, OOH, SORRY,
YOU SMELL LIKE BEN.

19:14.903 --> 19:16.864
{\an3}COME ON, LET'S GET YOU OUT OF
THOSE AWESOME LEG WARMERS

19:16.947 --> 19:19.908
{\an6}AND OVER TO THE HIPPIE
SO WE CAN FIX THIS BEFORE
BEN MISSES HIS BIG CHANCE.

19:19.992 --> 19:20.576
[GROWLING]

19:20.659 --> 19:23.954
[BARKING/TALKING]

19:24.037 --> 19:26.164
HAPPY, WHAT HAS GOTTEN INTO YOU?

19:26.248 --> 19:29.084
BEN HAS BEEN PREPARING FOR THIS
AUDITION SINCE LAST YEAR.

19:29.167 --> 19:31.336
[GROWLING PROTEST]

19:31.420 --> 19:32.254
[WHIMPERING]

19:32.337 --> 19:33.088
Ben: COME ON,
THERE'S NO TIME.

19:33.172 --> 19:36.592
THE AUDITION'S
GONNA START SOON.

19:36.675 --> 19:40.262
{\an6}FINE, YOU TWO
STAY HERE AND GET IN LINE
FOR THE AUDITION.

19:40.345 --> 19:42.556
LISTEN, BEN, WAIT...

19:42.639 --> 19:44.057
{\an1}BEN, I...

19:44.141 --> 19:45.893
OH, OK.

19:45.976 --> 19:49.104
I'LL BE RIGHT BACK.

19:49.187 --> 19:50.355
PLEASE EXPLAIN TO ME AGAIN

19:50.439 --> 19:52.900
HOW A GROWN MAN MISTAKES
A BOX OF REGULAR TAQUITOS

19:52.983 --> 19:54.818
FOR A BOX OF MAGIC-QUITOS?

19:54.902 --> 19:56.653
{\an3}A BABY CAN
TELL THE DIFFERENCE.

19:56.737 --> 19:59.031
[SIGHS]

19:59.114 --> 20:00.908
I'M SORRY, MAN.

20:00.991 --> 20:03.619
{\an5}I SWEAR, I'D TAKE IT
ALL BACK IF I KNEW WHAT
YOU WERE TALKING ABOUT.

20:03.702 --> 20:06.872
[PIANO PLAYS]

20:06.955 --> 20:09.708
Children: ♪ LA-LA-LA,
LA, LA, LA, LA ♪

20:09.791 --> 20:12.002
♪ LA-LA-LA,
LA, LA, LA, LA ♪

20:12.085 --> 20:13.295
[CLEARS THROAT]

20:13.378 --> 20:15.714
[HOWLING]: ♪ LA-LA-LA,
LA, LA, LA, LA ♪

20:15.797 --> 20:19.968
[HOWLING CONTINUES]

20:20.052 --> 20:20.594
[PANTING]

20:20.677 --> 20:21.803
COME ON, BESSIE.

20:21.887 --> 20:23.347
WHERE ARE YOU?

20:28.060 --> 20:29.937
[ORGAN PLAYS
"THE ANNIVERSARY SONG"]

20:33.398 --> 20:34.858
[SCREECHING]

20:43.575 --> 20:44.618
[MICROWAVE BEEPS]

20:44.701 --> 20:46.244
Hippie: OHH...

20:46.328 --> 20:48.330
[LAUGHS] WHOA, MAN.

20:48.413 --> 20:50.999
I'M WEARING A SASH.

20:51.083 --> 20:52.042
Bessie: OH, BOY.

20:52.125 --> 20:54.294
[GAGGING]

20:54.378 --> 20:57.464
{\an3}ACH, HOW CAN YOU
BREATHE IN THIS THING?

20:57.547 --> 20:58.340
OH, YEAH, SEE
WHAT I DO IS...

20:58.423 --> 21:00.968
JUST GRAB THE TACQUITO
AND LET'S GO.

21:01.051 --> 21:02.678
WE GOTTA SWITCH BACK
"HEN AND BAPPY."

21:02.761 --> 21:05.263
UM, NEXT UP, 16?

21:05.889 --> 21:08.183
GIVE IT, MINE...

21:08.266 --> 21:11.186
[GROWLING AND GROANING]

21:11.269 --> 21:12.145
16?

21:12.229 --> 21:13.981
{\an1}...16?

21:14.064 --> 21:17.275
Bessie: I'M HERE JUST IN TIME.

21:17.359 --> 21:20.237
NOW THEN, WHO AMONG YOU SCAMPS
WANTS PORRIDGE?

21:20.320 --> 21:22.030
[CLEARS THROAT]

21:22.114 --> 21:23.782
[PLAINTIVE BARKING]

21:23.865 --> 21:27.577
[DRAMATIC WHIMPERING...]

21:36.628 --> 21:37.879
YOU'RE...

21:37.963 --> 21:39.256
...BRILLIANT.

21:39.339 --> 21:42.175
I'VE NEVER SEEN IT PERFORMED
WITH SUCH DARING.

21:42.259 --> 21:43.051
YOU'VE GOT THE PART.

21:43.135 --> 21:44.678
AH!

21:44.761 --> 21:46.430
[GRUNTS] AH, OOH.

21:46.513 --> 21:49.057
Bessie: BEN, I TRIED,
I'M SORRY.

21:49.141 --> 21:50.559
[PANTING]

21:50.642 --> 21:52.019
I... I GOT IT?

21:52.102 --> 21:55.188
I GOT THE PART.

21:55.272 --> 21:55.814
HEY, WAIT.

21:55.897 --> 21:58.025
[HIPPIE LAUGHING]

21:58.108 --> 21:58.608
Hippie: ALL'S WELL
THAT ENDS WELLS.

21:58.692 --> 22:00.652
All: HOORAY.

22:00.736 --> 22:03.196
[COW MOOS]

22:03.280 --> 22:04.281
[BARKING]

22:10.662 --> 22:12.122
[GROWLING]

22:13.206 --> 22:16.334
[♪...]

22:53.121 --> 22:54.956
[CHILDREN GIGGLING]

22:55.040 --> 22:57.375
[CHILDREN LAUGHING]
